      <feature>
        <name>Favored Enemy</name>
        <text>You always have the Hunter's Mark spell prepared. You can cast it twice without expending a spell slot. and you regain all expended uses of this ability when you finish a Long Rest.

The number of times you can cast the spell without a spell slot increases when you reach certain Ranger levels, as shown in the Favored Enemy column of the Ranger Features table.

Source:	Player's Handbook 2024 p. 119</text>
